sql:
SELECT module_name, credit_hours
FROM modules
WHERE is_active = 1 AND LENGTH(module_name) > 5;

external_knowledge:
- 'actively teaching' refers to instructors who are currently assigned to teach at least one course and have not been deactivated; 
- 'accessed the system at least once in the last month' implies that the instructor has logged in or interacted with the system within the past 30 days;
- 'total feedback they have received' refers to the cumulative feedback from all courses taught by the instructor.
